# Local development can query Cloudflare D1/R2 through REST when native Worker bindings
# are not available in Vite dev. Put real values in .env.local only.
#
# Required in .env.local for local D1/R2 REST fallback:
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN or CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ACCESS_TOKEN
#
# Optional local overrides:
# QUESTION_DB_DATABASE_ID
# QUESTION_R2_BUCKET_NAME
